724418f-a.title: Manhattan: West Broadway - Houston Street (West)
724418f-a.text:
West Broadway, west side, south from and across
Bleecker Street, showing this thoroughfare subsecuent to
the demolition of the old Sixth Avenue ''El'' and its Bleecker
Street station. At the right is a curved iron front structure
that bears No's. 142 Bleecker Street and 510-16 West Broadway.
This is at the S.W. corner of this intersection.
May 19, 1939
P. L. Sperr

724413f-b.text:
West Broadway, south from West Houston Street,
showing individual photos of both sides of this thorough-
fare during and subsecuent to the ''El'' demolition.
The cleared areas in the foreground are part
of the ewath sliced off of Houston Street for the
Municipal Eighth Avenue Subway construction..

724497f-a.title: Manhattan: Houston Street - West Broadway
724497f-a.text:
West Houston Street, north side, at West Broadway, showing
both the N.E. (in Nos. 2 \& 3) and N.W. (No. 1) corners. The buildings
in the latter view bear No's 88 to 92 (from right to left). The
elevated system seen on West Broadway is the Sixth Ave. line. No. 3
of this set is eastward from the corner shown in View No. 2 (N.E.).
May 7, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
724497f-a.folder: Houston Street & West Broadway, Manhattan, NY

724498f-a.title: Manhattan: Houston Street (West - West Broadway
724498f-a.text:
Houston Street, south side, west from West Broadway (formerly South
Fifth Avenue). All the buildings shown on the south side of the
street are shortly to be razed to facilitate subway construction.
July 17, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
According to the New Eork Times of April 4, 1938 the City of
New York, Department of Markets will erect a 1-story structure to be
used as a Municipal Market on the site of buildings shown on the left
and which will extend 1 block, from West Broadway, to Thompson Street;
the site to include Nos. 89 to 105 West Houston Street and 160
Thompson Street.
